msgctxt "sn56.23:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Koṭigāmavagga "
msgstr "3. At the Village of Koṭi "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 23. Sammāsambuddhasutta → abhisambuddhasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn56.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Sammāsambuddhasutta "
msgstr "23. The Fully Awakened Buddha "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn56.23:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.23:1.2"
msgid "Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, ariyasaccāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four noble truths. "

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.3"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.4"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ—"
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.5"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri ariyasaccāni. "
msgstr "These are the four noble truths. "

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.6"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ yathābhūtaṃ abhisambuddhattā tathāgato ‘arahaṃ sammāsambuddho’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "It is because he has truly woken up to these four noble truths that the Realized One is called ‘the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn56.23:2.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.23:2.2"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
